==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prawn
<hw>Prawn</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>prane</ets>,
of unknown origin; cf. L. <ets>perna</ets> a sea mussel.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of large shrimplike
Crustacea having slender legs and long antenn⟦ae⟧. They mostly belong to
the genera <gen>Pandalus</gen>, <gen>Pal⟦ae⟧mon</gen>,
<gen>Pal⟦ae⟧monetes</gen>, and <gen>Peneus</gen>, and are much used as
food. The common English prawn is <spn>Pal⟦ae⟧mon
serratus</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The name is often applied to any large
shrimp.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

